tip.text: The worst piccolo I have had in a long time! Totally burnt. Avoid!
The best durian ice-cream in the world! Pure durian!
Hipster cafe close to Nowy Świat. Traditional Polish breakfast with a healthy twist. Good coffee. They have cold drip, filter and aeropress, aero-tonic.
The biggest, healthiest and tastiest avocado on toast in Singapore. Comes on real sourdough and with Kale. $10
OK piccolo, cool vibe. Turns into a bar at night. The food is horrible - not a single vegetarian or healthy option unless you want to eat tones of sugar!
Lots of healthy options including gluten free. The guava breton is to die for!

formattedAddress: #01–05, National Gallery Singapore (1 St Andrew's Road)

tip.text: The best degustation menu in Malaysia. Amazing attention to detail, flavor combination and presentation. 5 course menu (MYR 180) comes with 5 free additional mini-courses.
Massive French toast - half the brioche loaf. Good piccolo.
Great speakeasy
Bartender Chris is a well of knowledge on Taiwanese Whiskey
Good coffee and cool industrial vibe - Melbourne style!
A gem in Mongkok. Great beans roasted in-house and freshly baked croissants! Go for piccolo!

formattedAddress: 36-46 Hoi King St, Tai Kok Tsui, Kowloon, Hong Kong

tip.text: Great Hor Fun - very smoky. You can get it with fish or vegetarian.
Great Hor Fun - very smoky. You can get it with fish or vegetarian.
Great vibe on Friday night. Hip crowd, live band, outdoor seating, healthy bar food including vegan and gluten-free. Great cocktails.
Beautiful beach wit warm water and soft, milky white sand.
Amazing collection of Dali works. Download the free app for a free audio tour. Beautiful building.

formattedAddress: 1 Dali Blvd (at Bayshore Dr & 5th Av SE)

tip.text: Great beach and tiki bar.
Great vegan and gluten-free options. Try tempeh plato which comes with black beans, platano and spicy slaw or salad with jicama and tempeh. Great atmosphere, Latin music and hip area.
Pineapple bun with butter, crispy bun with condensed milk and milk tea with real condensed milk!

formattedAddress: Level 8, Departures, Terminal 1,Hong Kong International Airport, Chek Lap Kok

venue.name: Tsui Wah Restaurant 翠華餐廳 (翠華餐廳)

tip.text: This place is definitely not healthy. They use cheap Marigold juice, nothing is organic and the smoothies and bowls are sugar bombs! Avoid!
Decent piccolo latte with sour undertones. They should however use good quality full cream milk (organic) to make it perfect. Red Rabbit Coffee beans are used for espresso based drinks.
Horrible burnt coffee. Look how dark their version of piccolo is.
Amazing organic herbal tisanes (moringa, lemon grass). The best place for organic, healthy, gluten-free desserts and food made from local ingredients (rukau, mango, moringa). Relaxing setting.
Great little airport in paradise.
Paradise on earth! Take the vaka trip to One Foot Island!
Amazing sunset views! Real feet in the sand bar. Authentic!
At the moment - the best piccolo in Auckland.
Great food, good interior, excellent pomegranate cosmo. Butter could be better.
Great food for breakfast, lunch, dinner and dessert. Their sourdough bread with smoked butter is to die for. So is chocolate and coffee baklava. Coffee needs to be improved (really bad piccolo).
Eat-in or take-away. Good selection of Asian healthy food with Thai, Korean and Japanese influences.
Authentic Ethiopian food - try Doro Wot (chicken) or Yetsom Beyaynetu (vegetarian) with the traditional fermented panckake - enjera. You can also taste Ethiopian coffee.
Great selection of healthy, organic food: slow pressed juices, smoothies, gluten-free and vegan meals and raw cakes. Very good prices, too - $4.20 for dirty turmeric latte with plant milk.
Amazing views! You can drive up all the way to the peak!
Freshly renovated art deco hotel. Cozy, modern. Great location - walking distance to everywhere.
Cool modern bar. The best in Napier. Good wine selection and cocktails. Packed on Saturday nights from 6:30pm on.
Try their Fat Black (small long black with cacao butter), kimchi and alpaca paleo pie and chicken & noodle broth.
Horrible coffee. Burnt, over extracted. They seriously need to invest in training their baristas.
Horrible service. Slow and rude. The weekend brunch is seriously overpriced (EUR 30) considering it includes only one (!) drink - either coffee or juice and you are asked to leave after 2 hours.
Really nice lounge with lots of food and drink choices and flowing water helping you to telax. Grab some Krówki and Prince Polo before the flight!
Lots of craft beers - try the white beer from the region (from Dabrowa Białostocka)  - Białe Podlaskie with hops, coriander and orange peel. Spacious. Cozy. Hipster-ish.
Beautfil park. There is a light show at the fountains during summer evenings.
Really good food - lots of vegan and glutenfree options. Really bad flat white!
Great food and authentic rustic atmosphere. Try "kwas chlebowy" to drink and herring, pierogi and "nalesniki z maslem". Palce lizac!
Excellent flat white! Better than any cafe in London. They are using beans from allover the world and roasted in Krakow. Great breakfast and lunch menu.
The best dumplings (pierogi) in Poland! Made from scratch with tender, paper-thin skins & lightly sour cabbage and boletus filling! Super friendly & passionate owners. Local photos on the walls.
Piccolo out of balance. The place is trendy and popular. Loud music and good pasteis de nata.
It's in the knife-stabbing part of Shoreditch. Average piccolo. No healthy food options. If you are into dairy and gluten go for a cheese toastie (£5)
The piccolo is out of balance.
The best coffee in London. Try Guatemala short macchiato. Excellent roast and good baristas. Sister outlet of New Plymouth cafe. Food needs to be improved - burnt bread and hard poached eggs.
Amazing seafood! All locally sourced! Try the grey mullet with zucchini flower stuffed with lobster. Yum! And the espresso sour cherry martini for dessert.
Excellent piccolo! One of the best I have ever had.
Very professional. Amazing views! No fear!
Great coffee and knowledgeable barista. They use L'Affare beans. The herbal and fruit teas are hand picked by a herbalist. Try a flat white with Little Island Coconut Milk.
Take an Explore ferry from Paihia to get here and spend half a day picnicking, chilling out at a bar/cafe, hiking, kayaking, paddle boarding.
I can't believe there are still places serving supermarket bread as a base of all their breakfast dishes. Underwhelming food. Long wait. Avoid!
"How many shots in your flat white?" That sums is up all. Horrible coffee. They poured flat white and latte in exactly the same way, with the same amount of milk. Buy your coffee at El Cafe instead.
Beautiful bungalows built in Kanak way. Access to the beach and free water sports equipment. Lots of hikes around the hotel and boat trips to the reef.
Grab a coffee and breakfast in a Caldoche way - espresso or noisette and a croissant or pain au chocolat, fruit juice, croque madame, etc. bustling with local life.
Beautiful hotel. Swimming pool with a sea view. Free Water Sports equipment. Bungalows with private terraces. Good breakfast. 15min walk to Piscine Naturelle with the best snorkeling on the island.
Beautiful view from the balcony, nicely appointed rooms, great pool and direct access to the beach.
Great breakfast - try noisette coffee and fresh bread basket!
Amazing lounge! Tattinger and Mumm, good French red and white wine, Zubrówka. Little snacks. Beautiful design and view!
Perfect spot for jumps!
Amazing beach. Great surf.

Horrible service. I waited 15min for the coffee, had to go back to the counter to ask for it. The coffee was delivered 5min later with no apology. The piccolo was burnt. Avoid! There are better places

location.address: Shop 3023, 3/F, IFC Mall, 1 Harbour View St
formattedAddress: Shop 3023, 3/F, IFC Mall, 1 Harbour View St

tip.text: Amazing raw food place. Great service and atmosphere, good music. Relaxing. Wide range of raw, vegan, gluten free and sugar free dishes, smoothies, juices and desserts.
Similar menu to Dear Jervois. Good long black. Lots of glutenfree options. Freedom Loaf. Vegan, raw cakes in the cabinet.
All their wines are organic. Try the pinot noir and dry riesling.
Really good cocktails. Guest batman appearance from around the globe!
Nice interior but average food. Menu has not been updated (they have not had rye bread for ages). Instead of a piccolo they serve a latte size glass with so little coffee you can hardly taste it.
Always interesting exhibitions with great audio guides. Check out Warhol - Wei Wei before it closes down on 24 April 2016.
Excellent coffee. Perfect piccolo. Amazing food. Plenty of vegan and gluten-free options as well. Top 3 cafe in Melbourne. Highly recommended!

formattedAddress: 18 Yarra Pl (btwn York St & Coventry St)

tip.text: Great view!
This cafe discriminates against disabled - the staff refused to give a table to a disables person (you need to wait at least 40 minutes) although there were 4 free tables.
Awesome! Really well organized and safe. The city belongs to people :-)
Amazing cannelloni - share with two other people as they are huge.
Smoothies, juices, raw meals and desserts. Good but not as creative as other raw cafes/restaurants in the world (i.e. Little Bird in Auckland).
Their Photography Cocktail cones with a polaroid photo of you!
Really good piccolo. The right proportions and the right cup size.
Good coffee, although piccolo is served in a flat white cup and it's a double shot espresso amd not ristretto based.
Avoid! The owner is into money rather than wine. He only makes standard wines because they sell. Sauvignon blanc tastes like tobacco. Other wines don't taste good either.
Good piccolo latte.
Beautiful outdoor seating. Organically made wines - their dry riesling and pinot noir are a must!
Great food and service. Outdoor patio with shade and greenery. Paleo and vegan menu. Their shakshuka eggs (paleo) and yemenite bread are a must!
Magical place.
Beautiful and affordable sculptures for home and garden from a local New Zealand artist.
Short walk via limestone to a platform with a great view!
Great view! You can read about Abel Tasman's voyage to New Zealand.
Decent coffee - they roast their own beans under Rabbit Island Coffee Co. brand. Lots of healthy, gluten-free, vegan, raw and refined sugar free options. Try açai bowl!
Opened in Jan'16, serving decent piccolo (the best you can get in Nelson) and gluten-free scrolls & brownies (also refined sugar free). No breakfast or lunch menu.

Horrible piccolo - huge and it tastes like there is no milk. The place looks like a car workshop from the outside. Takeaway cups only while plenty of space to seat inside. Not environmentally friendly
Don't be fooled by reviews on TripAdvisor. Rooms are expensive ($250!), small and run down and there is constant noise from the road. It feels like you are sleeping on the highway. Don't stay here!
Amazing black sand beach. Stretches for kilometers. You can get a permit online and drive on it.
Amazing sunsets. Good beach for a swim as it's in the bay - the water is warm and calm.
Lots of gluten-free, sugar-free, dairy-free and raw options. Ozone Coffee Beans. They carry their cold brew as well.
Interesting Gallery with a shop where y u can buy ceramics and jewelry made by local artists.
Amazing sunset!
New kid on the block (opened in Jan 2016) serving atomic coffee. Cool fit-out. Good for takeaway as there are no tables inside/outside. Only standing space.
Really bad coffee. The roastery (eightthirty) and coffee machine provider (La Marzocco) should have provided them with a proper training. No wonder the place is empty.
The best piccolo in Kuala Lumpur. Well balanced. Great, innovative fusion food - try their barley risotto with dried shrimp and curry leaves.
Really good piccolo and healthy menu - organic eggs from the hill tribes, almond milk. House baked sourdough and rye bread. No gluten-free bread yet but there are salads and soups.

tip.text: Amazing view! Good organic wine but it's not mind-blowing.
Amazing dawn and sunset.
Amazing view from the terrace! Good quality fish and chips although the portion is too small considering the price (NZD 20).
Horrible coffee. All breakfast choices have either gluten or dairy in them. There is a raw blueberry cheesecake in the cabinet though.

Amazing degustation menu. 7 courses for only $89. Appetizers in a layered box,  locally sourced ingredients (fish, ginger, oysters). Japanese take on fish & chips is great, so is whitebait chawanmushi
Excellent piccolo. Better than in the central location.
Still the best piccolo in Hong Kong. The proportions are perfect and the taste well balanced. Better than the piccolo at the cupping room (too big). Cozy setting. Top cafe in Hong Kong.
Amazing dim sum in a serene setting. Best way to get away from the bustle and hustle. All is vegetarian and most gluten-free!

formattedAddress: G/F, The K.S. Lo Gallery, Hong Kong Park

venue.name: Lock Cha Tea House 樂茶軒

tip.text: The only place in Nadi serving local Fijian cuisine. The food is amazing! Made from organic, fresh, local ingredients. Try kokoda, vakalolo and cassava chips. All gluten-free, dairy-free and paleo!
Great organic, raw, gluten-free, plant-based food. Try their rolls, smoothies and cakes.
Their food tastes amazing and is super healthy! The amount f effort out in preparation is not reflected in low prices. Raspberry cacao brownie $6 is an all time favorite!
Really bad coffee. OK juices but not all of them are made from scratch and most are high on fructose as they all contain fruit or even dairy (skyr).
Good location - walking distance to Star Ferry and MTR.

venue.name: Sheraton Hong Kong Hotel & Towers (香港喜來登酒店)

tip.text: Truly disappointing! No freedom loaf and no Carew almond milk. The staff don't know the menu.
Burnt is an understatement. Sacrilege to La Marzocco and Eight Thirty Beans they are using.
Perfect Carew Kitchen Almond Milk Flat White.
Good coffee. Decent piccolo. Atomic Beans.
Nice decor but They just don't get the concept of the single shot - still pour the same amount of water so the piccolo comes out awful. It's all about balance...
Fun experience (2hr guided tour with a complimentary beer/cider/ginger beer at the end at Green Dragon. A bit too pricey (NZD 75 per person).
Bad coffee (burnt) and only cabinet food - no gluten-free, sugar-free, clean eating options. Avoid.
Too expensive for what it is. Run down, dirty shacks with very low water pressure and leaking taps. There is nothing to do on the island. And it's takes a 40min boat ride from Nukualofa to get there.

venue.name: Royal Sunset Island Resort Atata Island

tip.text: Local watering whole for the people working around the port. Brisk service - they will change your beer glass before you ever notice. They don't carry Outrigger Lager though - the best local beer.
The rooms are nice and clean but the water pressure low, the walls paper thin (you can hear the neighbours snoring) and the service arrogant. The street outside is very noisy!
The worst flat white in the whole of Tonga.
Coffee is not good by any means but it's the best in Nukualofa. They use Tongan beans and have flat white. The food is great though - try Tongan ceviche.
Best to see in the morning sun. But be careful on Saturday morning before 7:30am - lots of suspicious types - drunks, homeless in the park around

Best Raw restaurant in Copenhagen. Everything is vegan, gluten-free & sugar free. They serve breakfast, sandwiches, salad, lasagna, thai noodles, desserts, juices, smoothies and coffee. Modern design.
The smallest hotel bed ever! It's smaller than the one I had as a child!
Great place for breakfast. They have different sets including tea/coffee. Great selection of teas!
The Best Ice-Cream in Belgium!
Excellent piccolo (cortado). They source and roast their own beans. You can also get fresh ginger and lemon and yoghurt & granola for breakfast.
Amazing views, great walks and treks around it. Perfect fishing spot. Mix of azure blue water, black sand and lush greenery.
Average food. Really bad coffee - looks great but it's burnt and over-extracted.
Amazing view!
Amazing selection of smoothies, home-made nut mylks, healthy breakfast and lunch options - all healthy, gluten-free, dairyfree and sugarfree. Lots of vegan meals. Raw desserts. Heaven!
Big space - looks looks school canteen. Not cozy at all. Good latte art but the coffee was over-extracted.
The Best Gelato in Southern Hemisphere. Better than Messina from Sydney. True Haute-Cuisine Ice-cream. Great service!
Little hole in the wall serving decent coffee. Rocket beans - currently 65% Colombia Finca La Falda and 35% Tanzania Tweega. Unfortunately their piccolo is based on double shot espresso.
Great beans and good long black. Unfortunately standard piccolo comes as a double shot.
Great performance during Matariki 2015 - Hawaiki Tu.
Beautiful setting. You can go inside and walk upstairs to a terrace around the lighthouse.
Little Organic Grocer and Cafe in the centre of Auckland. Not everything on the menu is healthy though.
Great setting. OK food. Terrible coffee. I:Where are the beans from? S: (blank look) I: Coffee Beans S: Let me check (after checking) From Pnsonby I: (look of horror)
